Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef cooks, trim the @Green Beans{150%g}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} and green beans.

Bring back to the boil, then cook until tender, ~{4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> Run the noodles and veg under cold water to stop them sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Lime{1/2} and cut into wedges.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Once the beef is cooked, stir in the garlic and @Ginger Puree{15%g}. Fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{96%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%g} and @Tomato Ketchup{2%tsp} to the beef.

Bring to the boil, stirring, then lower the heat.

Simmer until thickened and sticky, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the cooked noodles and green beans to the #pan{} and mix to coat in the sticky sauce.

Squeeze in the lime juice.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share your sticky noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!